      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=89<!-- =CF=89 --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega }</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/48eff443f9de7a985bb94ca3bde20813ea737be8" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.446ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \om=
ega }"></span> (<span title=3D"Polytonic Greek" class=3D"polytonic">=CF=89<=
/span>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omega" title=3D"Omega">ome=
ga</a>).
</p><p>Set theory was beginning to become an essential ingredient of the ne=
w =E2=80=9Cmodern=E2=80=9D approach to mathematics. Originally, Cantor's th=
eory of transfinite numbers was regarded as counter-intuitive&nbsp;=E2=80=
=93 even shocking. This caused it to encounter resistance from mathematical=
 contemporaries such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leopold_Kr=
onecker" title=3D"Leopold Kronecker">Leopold Kronecker</a> and <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Poincar%C3%A9" title=3D"Henri Poincar=C3=
=A9">Henri Poincar=C3=A9</a> and later from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Hermann_Weyl" title=3D"Hermann Weyl">Hermann Weyl</a> and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L._E._J._Brouwer" title=3D"L. E. J. Brouw=
er">L. E. J. Brouwer</a>, while <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lu=
dwig_Wittgenstein" title=3D"Ludwig Wittgenstein">Ludwig Wittgenstein</a> ra=
ised <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_objections_to_C=
antor%27s_theory" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Philosophical objections t=
o Cantor's theory">philosophical objections</a> (see: <i><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Controversy_over_Cantor%27s_theory" title=3D"Controv=
ersy over Cantor's theory">Controversy over Cantor's theory</a></i>).<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Set_theory#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>a<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-left" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Young_frege.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-description"=
><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Youn=
